### PingSSO Spring Boot API Testing
### REST Client file for testing AuthController endpoints
### Install "REST Client" extension by Huachao Mou to use this file

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@apiPrefix = /api/auth

### Variables for storing response data
@sessionId = 
@bearerToken = 
@userId = 1
@email = test@example.com

### ==================================
### 1. LOGIN ENDPOINT
### ==================================

### Login with PingSSO profile
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "pingSsoId": "pingsso-123456",
  "name": "Test User",
  "picture": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg"
}

@name Login

### ==================================
### 2. CALLBACK ENDPOINT
### ==================================

### Handle OAuth callback from PingSSO
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/callback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userInfo": {
    "sub": "pingsso-callback-123",
    "email": "callback@example.com",
    "name": "Callback User",
    "picture": "https://example.com/callback-avatar.jpg"
  }
}

@name OAuth Callback

### ==================================
### 3. SESSION ENDPOINTS
### ==================================

### Get active sessions (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}

@name Get Active Sessions

### Get session information (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/session-info
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}
Cookie: PINGSSO_SESSION={{sessionId}}

@name Get Session Info

### Revoke a specific session (requires authentication)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/revoke
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}

@name Revoke Session

### ==================================
### 4. USER ENDPOINTS
### ==================================

### Get user information by email
GET {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/user-info?email={{email}}

@name Get User Info

### ==================================
### 5. TOKEN ENDPOINTS
### ==================================

### Generate a new bearer token (requires authentication)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/token
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}

@name Generate Token

### ==================================
### 6. LOGOUT ENDPOINTS
### ==================================

### Logout (invalidate current session)
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}
Cookie: PINGSSO_SESSION={{sessionId}}

@name Logout

### Logout all sessions for the user
POST {{baseUrl}}{{apiPrefix}}/logout-all
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}

@name Logout All Sessions

### ==================================
### USAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
### ==================================
### 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code
### 2. Update @baseUrl, @email, @sessionId, and @bearerToken variables
### 3. Click "Send Request" above each request to execute
### 4. Responses will appear in a side panel
### 5. Successful login will return sessionId and bearerToken
### 6. Copy those values to the variables above for authenticated requests
